Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.70,0:00:03.37,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A racing second hand, a shooting comet!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.37,0:00:07.20,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Conan's logic works great\Non hearts tired by modern society!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.20,0:00:10.97,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Today's case is a midsummer night!\NI crush the culprit's dreams!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.97,0:00:12.51,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He sees the single truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.51,0:00:14.64,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and looks like a kid but has the mind of an adult.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.64,0:00:16.93,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.01,0:01:44.47,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Izu
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.34,0:01:47.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Summer! You got your sun and your ocean!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.05,0:01:53.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Still, I can't believe Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s the only boy on the beach
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.02,0:01:57.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,when there's two hot girls here! How pathetic...!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.62,0:01:59.49,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Well, excuse me!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.49,0:02:04.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Obviously! This is your villa's private beach!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.13,0:02:05.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.30,0:02:11.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're here to get a great tan and catch guys all summer long!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.04,0:02:14.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're always talking about guys, Sonoko...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.71,0:02:18.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It must be nice to know who your husband'll be!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.61,0:02:24.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You bought that swimsuit\Nto show Shin'ichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.32,0:02:28.82,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That... was for me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.82,0:02:31.66,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Since I'm here, I'll get a closer look!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.93,0:02:36.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yuzo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.28,0:02:37.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Young girls are so nice!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.90,0:02:41.82,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Yuzo Tomizawa (28)\NAyako's Fiancée
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.26,0:02:41.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I shouldn't have gotten engaged yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.17,0:02:45.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, you! You're supposed to be in love with my sister!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.77,0:02:47.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So he's—
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.12,0:02:47.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yep!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.87,0:02:53.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yuzo Tomizawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, third son of the head of Tomizawa Industries!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.31,0:02:56.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's marrying my sister in the fall!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.12,0:02:59.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Our two family companies are really close!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.63,0:03:01.76,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Tomizawa Family Villa
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.63,0:03:01.76,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Suzuki Family Villa
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.75,0:03:02.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look! Even our villas are next to each other!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.75,0:03:08.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He saw my sister at a party and had love at first sight!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.59,0:03:10.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're embarrassing me, Sonoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.72,0:03:14.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's in our villa if you're looking for her...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.76,0:03:20.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, I'm here to introduce her to my father and brothers...!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.40,0:03:21.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So then—
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.28,0:03:22.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're all coming?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.97,0:03:25.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. My brothers arrive tomorrow,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.84,0:03:28.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but my father should be at the villa by now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.84,0:03:30.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll give him a call.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.61,0:03:36.92,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}This is the Tomizawa residence.\NWe're not home right now,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.92,0:03:39.69,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}so please leave a message after the beep—
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.69,0:03:42.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? It's the machine...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.16,0:03:44.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you have the time?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.20,0:03:45.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,3:10...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.79,0:03:49.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's weird. He was supposed to be there at 3:00...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.42,0:03:51.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's wrong, Sonoko?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.82,0:03:55.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tetsuhara{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-ojisama{\r} is coming!\NThis is no time to play in the ocean!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.76,0:03:57.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have to greet him!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.40,0:03:58.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait! Sonoko!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.56,0:04:05.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.66,0:04:07.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad...!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.43,0:04:10.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, Yuzo! I came over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.63,0:04:16.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ugh! I said to wait in the villa for me to bring her there!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.38,0:04:18.67,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Tetsuhara Tomizawa (60)\NPresident of Tomizawa Industries
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.64,0:04:22.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought we might enjoy your future wife's cooking tonight...!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.63,0:04:22.34,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Ayako Suzuki\NSonoko's Sister
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.93,0:04:24.50,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He sent it flying!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.50,0:04:31.24,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It's gone! Three runs! Kogure sent it\Ninto the right stands in the rain!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.24,0:04:32.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.47,0:04:35.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad. You're sure a big Kogure fan...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.81,0:04:37.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I sure am!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.28,0:04:40.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But you didn't have to watch him here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.15,0:04:45.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I had no choice. I'm getting bad satellite reception.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.22,0:04:51.49,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A pop fly down the center!\NThe Falcons are on fire now!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.49,0:04:57.50,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It's 9:00, so we bring you a 5-minute news break!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.50,0:05:02.40,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Typhoon 11 has intensified and\Nis moving northward from Okinawa.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.40,0:05:06.47,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}As a result, many planes and boats are delayed.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.47,0:05:08.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,9:00? It's only the 6th inning...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.90,0:05:11.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The rain kept delaying the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.45,0:05:15.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ayako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}. Might you have a radio?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.52,0:05:19.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It doesn't look like that game's on the radio...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.65,0:05:25.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, now! It'll begin soon!\NHow about some coffee?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.96,0:05:29.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Suzuki women are so considerate!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.63,0:05:32.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yuzo! You're one lucky guy!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.80,0:05:36.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My other two sons, on the other hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.47,0:05:42.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Taichi, the oldest, ditched the business and became a novelist instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.48,0:05:44.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So he's still single.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.41,0:05:47.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tatsuji, the middle son, joined the company
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.21,0:05:51.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but got engaged with some nobody without my consent!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.38,0:05:54.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stop talking bad about them...!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.35,0:05:58.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You too, Yuzo! With your stupid paintings and all...!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.33,0:06:00.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yuzo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.69,0:06:06.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll be in my studio. I have an illustration to finish.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.10,0:06:08.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yuzo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.00,0:06:10.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If only he'd quit being stubborn and join the business,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.84,0:06:12.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'd give him a good position!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.01,0:06:22.68,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It's over! The Falcons finally win 9-8 in the 11th inning!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.68,0:06:24.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes! Alright! Hurray!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.79,0:06:28.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}This{\i0} is the essence of Falcons baseball!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.49,0:06:33.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, look at the time. I should get back to my villa.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.60,0:06:39.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Alright, Ayako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}. I'll bring my sons over tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.70,0:06:41.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.22,0:06:42.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.67,0:06:49.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez! I wonder if he plans to watch another night game tomorrow...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.24,0:06:54.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, it's already 11:30. We should—
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.95,0:06:56.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A power failure?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.40,0:06:57.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looks like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.95,0:07:03.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See? The lights are out in the other villa...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.09,0:07:04.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It must've been the lightning!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.73,0:07:09.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.00,0:07:10.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone's there!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.17,0:07:11.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.67,0:07:13.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's he doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.57,0:07:20.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-Yuzo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.14,0:07:24.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.91,0:07:26.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.92,0:07:31.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}! Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.09,0:07:38.79,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Darn it! I lost him!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.33,0:07:43.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.73,0:07:46.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sir! Sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.07,0:07:54.56,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What the...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.36,0:07:59.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.90,0:08:05.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you witnessed Mr. Tomizawa being murdered by his son Yuzo
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.97,0:08:07.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,at 11:30 last night?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.77,0:08:09.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.84,0:08:13.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ayako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}. What's all this about?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.91,0:08:16.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yuzo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.35,0:08:18.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yuzo Tomizawa?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.28,0:08:19.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.02,0:08:20.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did something happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.55,0:08:24.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know full well you killed your own father!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.16,0:08:27.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh?! Dad?! That's crazy...!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.93,0:08:31.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! Let go! I didn't kill him!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.36,0:08:33.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's going on, Yuzo?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.09,0:08:37.30,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Tatsuji Tomizawa (28)\NOffice Worker
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.30,0:08:35.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tatsuji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-niisan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.77,0:08:37.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's all the ruckus?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.20,0:08:41.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Taichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-aniki{\r}! Looks like something happened!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.85,0:08:45.73,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Taichi Tomizawa (28)\NNovelist
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.11,0:08:45.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perfect timing. I need an idea for a new novel...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.73,0:08:49.73,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}T-Triplets?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.73,0:08:54.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yuzo Tomizawa! You're under arrest for the murder of your father!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.00,0:08:56.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective! Please wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.33,0:09:00.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We did see the killer's face...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.60,0:09:03.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But we only saw his eyes and nose!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.71,0:09:09.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We didn't know Yuzo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had two identical twins!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.85,0:09:14.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which means it was one of you three...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.22,0:09:19.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was in Okinawa last night on a business trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.22,0:09:22.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I took the first flight out and landed at Haneda 3 hours ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.96,0:09:27.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The last flight to Okinawa leaves at 8:00 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.30,0:09:30.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I couldn't have been at the villa when it happened!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.70,0:09:32.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Check it out!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.40,0:09:34.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.14,0:09:36.61,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I thought Okinawa was—
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.61,0:09:41.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, Detective. I'm not sure I can call it an alibi, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.94,0:09:45.01,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}You have two messages.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.01,0:09:46.90,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Do you have the time?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.90,0:09:48.68,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}3:10...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.68,0:09:53.49,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That's weird. He was supposed to be there at 3:00...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.49,0:09:55.42,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}3:10 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.42,0:09:59.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was me! I called from the beach!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.23,0:10:01.36,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Hello, this is Taichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.36,0:10:02.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here's mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.90,0:10:06.17,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Glad to see the Falcons won, Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.17,0:10:10.91,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Kogure pulled that homer to the right in the bottom of the 6th!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.91,0:10:15.51,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What a batter! Well, see you tomorrow!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.51,0:10:18.71,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}11:34 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.71,0:10:24.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,11:34 PM... The time the murder took place.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.15,0:10:28.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're certain it happened around 11:30?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.29,0:10:33.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes! I had checked the clock before we saw the killer!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.56,0:10:39.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Doesn't look like he did it!\NThat game was only on satellite!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.20,0:10:42.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It ended just after 11:25.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.30,0:10:45.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He couldn't have known how it ended unless he watched it all!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.61,0:10:48.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Confirm that with the TV and radio stations! Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.98,0:10:50.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.11,0:10:53.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, if neither of us is the killer...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.47,0:10:55.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yuzo's the only possibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.58,0:10:57.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,B-Brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.12,0:10:59.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No! I'd never kill anyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.55,0:11:02.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then where were you last night?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.09,0:11:04.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was in my studio the whole time.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.43,0:11:10.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes! A fellow illustrator called and woke me up! Just after 11:30!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.57,0:11:12.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He woke you up?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.10,0:11:13.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.00,0:11:17.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I dozed off! I had to pull an all-nighter to finish this job...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.61,0:11:19.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then we'll check with him!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.71,0:11:24.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective Yokomizo! About that passenger list...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.98,0:11:31.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? My name was there, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.17,0:11:33.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.76,0:11:37.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The issue is the time the plane landed!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.33,0:11:43.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The plane you were supposedly on landed at Haneda 30 minutes ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.73,0:11:45.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That can't be...!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.40,0:11:49.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess the typhoon delayed it! They said so on the news last night!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.64,0:11:51.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, you're right!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.41,0:11:56.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How about you tell us where you {\i1}really{\i0} were last night?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.08,0:12:01.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tokyo...! That's right!\NI returned to Tokyo last night!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.92,0:12:03.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To Hiromi's place in Tokyo!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.95,0:12:04.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hiromi...?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.89,0:12:09.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My fiancée. I heard she had collapsed...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.83,0:12:13.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't want my dad to find out I dropped work for her,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.83,0:12:16.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so I had someone cover for me!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.00,0:12:18.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the truth! Please believe me!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.00,0:12:19.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can anyone vouch for this?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.67,0:12:20.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hiromi.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.94,0:12:24.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah! I just mentioned how the game ended!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.44,0:12:28.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No news programs were covering it at 11:30!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.68,0:12:33.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I know, because I flipped channels, hoping to see that home run again!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.58,0:12:36.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective Yokomizo. He's telling the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.85,0:12:42.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was after midnight when TV and radio stations covered the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.26,0:12:46.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, are you a fan of Kogure?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.16,0:12:49.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were praising him on the phone!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.53,0:12:56.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's awesome! Only he could hit a home run into the right stands!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.24,0:12:59.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hit?! Explain yourself, Taichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.64,0:13:02.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You said he pulled it to the right on the phone!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.78,0:13:06.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Were you {\i1}really{\i0} watching that game?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.38,0:13:08.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Guess the truth's out.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.20,0:13:11.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So {\i1}you{\i0} killed your father?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.02,0:13:17.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nothing of the sort! I meant that I didn't see the game on TV.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.66,0:13:22.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I listened to it all on the radio\Nwhile playing pachinko.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.96,0:13:26.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was taking a break from writing...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.50,0:13:31.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess the only radio broadcast was in Osaka, where I live.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.04,0:13:35.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's right, only one radio station in Osaka aired that game.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.38,0:13:40.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Besides, I left a message at the time of the murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.42,0:13:43.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's true...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.02,0:13:48.12,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Who is it?! One of those three is lying!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.12,0:13:52.43,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And the victim's missing watch bugs me!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.43,0:13:54.76,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Why would the killer take it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.76,0:13:57.93,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}To keep the time a secret? Or—
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.93,0:14:00.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? This VCR is blinking!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.60,0:14:05.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, there was a 10-minute blackout at 11:30 last night!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.44,0:14:09.64,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Oh, yeah! There was a blackout just before the murder!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.64,0:14:11.25,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A blackout?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.25,0:14:15.08,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Wait, this is strange! What he said is impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.08,0:14:17.65,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And at the time, it was—
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.65,0:14:21.09,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Then the watch taken from the victim was...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.89,0:14:23.19,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Could it be?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.19,0:14:29.26,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}No doubt about it! The killer is the one telling two lies!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.74,0:14:37.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have to ask all three of you down to the station!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.81,0:14:39.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But...!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.41,0:14:41.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, this isn't funny!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.60,0:14:42.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why me?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.81,0:14:44.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We have no choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.95,0:14:50.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,These folks saw the killer's face\Njust after the murder!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.59,0:14:53.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One that looked just like you three!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.99,0:14:59.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, one of you killed your father!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.50,0:15:05.27,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I know who did it! It's definitely the one with the strange alibi!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.27,0:15:09.17,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Alright! I'll knock Sonoko out and make her a detective!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.84,0:15:11.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What're you doing, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.98,0:15:14.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's with this watch?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.88,0:15:16.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's—
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.28,0:15:18.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.05,0:15:21.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was aiming a weird watch at you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.68,0:15:25.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a toy! Dr. Agasa gave it to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.89,0:15:28.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A BB comes out if you press a button!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.65,0:15:31.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're such a troublemaker!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.39,0:15:33.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I gotta use the bathroom!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.90,0:15:45.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sonoko?! Hey, Sonoko!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.24,0:15:51.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've figured it out. I know that he killed Tetsuhara{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-ojisama{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.48,0:15:57.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not one of the three has a clear alibi!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.29,0:16:01.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But there's one who's clearly lying!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.56,0:16:04.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The killer is Taichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.10,0:16:05.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Taichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.73,0:16:08.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sure, kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.00,0:16:12.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Interesting. But I was in an Osaka pachinko parlor.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.34,0:16:15.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't think I could've been here then.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.54,0:16:18.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A pachinko parlor at 11:30?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.74,0:16:21.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.21,0:16:25.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't you know that pachinko parlors
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.58,0:16:29.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,can only stay open until 11:00 PM?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.49,0:16:36.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, pachinko parlors are generally forbidden to operate past 11:00!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.13,0:16:38.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even in Osaka!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.03,0:16:41.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means you're lying!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.40,0:16:42.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My mistake!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.83,0:16:46.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I heard the broadcast in a taxi\Non my way home from the parlor...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.84,0:16:48.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Honestly?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.27,0:16:51.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't be like that. It was a simple mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.64,0:16:56.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Besides, I left a message when the murder took place!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.55,0:16:58.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How do you explain that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.69,0:17:00.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.55,0:17:05.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the major oversight\Nyou made during the murder!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.19,0:17:07.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.12,0:17:10.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You should know; you were there!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.19,0:17:14.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The power went out for 10 minutes at 11:30!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.80,0:17:18.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes! The answering machine wouldn't work without power!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.63,0:17:23.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Its batteries power the clock, but it can't record messages!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.44,0:17:29.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So what's your message doing there at 11:34?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.05,0:17:32.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But you could ask Yuzo the same thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.32,0:17:36.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said he got a call just after 11:30!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.45,0:17:38.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You don't know anything, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.45,0:17:42.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can still make calls during a power outage!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.16,0:17:43.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.73,0:17:49.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true. Telephones receive power through the phone lines.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.60,0:17:53.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone must've messed with the clock to frame me—
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.94,0:17:56.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no telling when you'd call.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.04,0:18:00.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nobody could've matched the times just right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.84,0:18:03.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, when the game ended, you left a message
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.45,0:18:07.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,on the machine whose clock you had set ahead in advance.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.95,0:18:11.09,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Glad to see the Falcons won, Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.09,0:18:15.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As if you left the message just when the murder happened!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.16,0:18:20.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then you turned the clock back,\Nand waited for your father to return.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.63,0:18:24.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your father, who came next door to see the game!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.93,0:18:28.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And that's when you killed him!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.30,0:18:32.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I couldn't have known when he'd return...!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.98,0:18:37.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, you knew. You used a transmitter to hear!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.48,0:18:39.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A transmitter?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.48,0:18:46.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I bugged your villa? Then go ahead and look! There won't be any!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.89,0:18:49.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nobody said you bugged the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.99,0:18:54.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't there something unnaturally missing from the victim?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.40,0:18:56.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His watch!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.13,0:18:59.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aha! With a bugged watch,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.07,0:19:03.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,he could keep tabs on both the victim and the game!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.27,0:19:07.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So the watch was taken to remove the evidence?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.08,0:19:08.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.74,0:19:11.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bugging the victim's watch,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.48,0:19:18.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and breaking his satellite receiver to make him come to my villa...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.19,0:19:21.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As his son, you could easily do this!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.99,0:19:27.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nice theory. I almost want to use it for a book.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.63,0:19:30.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it'd be a third-rate novel.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.07,0:19:35.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you have any proof that I changed the answering machine's clock?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.24,0:19:42.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The times match; even Yuzo's message had the right time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.11,0:19:44.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You talk big for having no proof—
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.76,0:19:46.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Quit playin' around!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.38,0:19:51.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The fake time and message on the answering machine
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.09,0:19:55.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,actually prove that you're the killer!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.83,0:19:58.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Brother...!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.35,0:19:59.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It can't be true...!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.13,0:20:01.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah! This must be a mistake!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.93,0:20:04.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You had no reason to kill Dad...!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.80,0:20:10.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stop that, Yuzo. I'm not the great brother you take me for.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.51,0:20:13.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Money. I wanted the old man's inheritance.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.94,0:20:16.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I could keep writing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.15,0:20:17.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Brother...!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.55,0:20:22.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Things got tough. I suddenly ran out of work and money...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.28,0:20:27.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I found out when I went to Dad for help...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.09,0:20:33.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He had pressured the publishers\Nto drop each job that came my way!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.53,0:20:38.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess he wanted me to quit and follow in his footsteps.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.80,0:20:40.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So then you—
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.60,0:20:45.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. I used his visit here to kill him.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.98,0:20:52.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's also why I sent him the bugged watch and broke his receiver.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.78,0:20:58.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yuzo. I was going to try pinning it on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.59,0:21:01.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To increase my share of the inheritance.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.09,0:21:05.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was all so I could keep writing my novels...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.69,0:21:09.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it seems I wrote a poor mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.30,0:21:13.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To think the power would go out just then...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.60,0:21:17.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess fact is stranger than fiction...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.51,0:21:23.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe I didn't have the skill to be a writer.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.64,0:22:59.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's with Sonoko? She's spacing out...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.61,0:23:04.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's probably relieved Yuzo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} wasn't the killer!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.85,0:23:08.38,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Uh oh. She's staring at her arm.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.38,0:23:12.29,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Don't tell me she noticed\NI shot a sleeping dart in it...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.29,0:23:14.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I failed...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.36,0:23:17.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What're you talking about? That was great detective work!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.09,0:23:18.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective work?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.49,0:23:20.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just look at my arm!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.56,0:23:23.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's totally white!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.03,0:23:28.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was supposed to get a tan and catch some guys!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.51,0:23:33.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I know, Ran! Let's go to a tanning salon!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.08,0:23:37.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not now! We have to give our statements at the police station!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.21,0:23:38.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What for?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.98,0:23:42.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What a dumb girl...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.47,0:23:48.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What the...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.51,0:23:49.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's an SOS!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.55,0:23:57.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everyone out of the boat! The tide's rising!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.69,0:24:01.52,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The waves are too high for us to swim out!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.56,0:24:05.69,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Darn it! This is like a maze!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.69,0:24:08.29,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Which way?! Which way do we go?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.53,0:24:14.49,Signs,,0,0,0,,Next Conan:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.49,0:24:19.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan's Hint: The Tide's Ebb and Flow
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.78,0:24:21.46,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Next time the Detective Boys come out!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.46,0:24:22.49,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,- I'm Ayumi!\N- I'm Genta!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.49,0:24:23.28,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,I'm Mitsuhiko!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.28,0:24:24.02,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,No, you're not.
